 Joshua Jacobs, on July 22, 2013 at 8:43 am said:		

Awesome real-world description of an MVP in practice. The way I think of it, and MVP allows you to black box important components of the value proposition. Within these black boxes are highly processes that are extremely unscalable in the long-term, but with a near 0 startup phase. 
Renting a plane or helicopter and hand-tuning the data is great short-term alternative to robots and software. 
Building a great landing page is a great complementary exercise as well.
