 Jugo Mirkovic (@JuTwitti), on July 22, 2013 at 1:06 pm said:		

Thanks allot for this reminder, it hit me like a hammer to my head.
You saved them from a bunch of frustration and grief. Wish I read this 6 months ago. We did the exact opposite, got caught up in the dev process and lost our focus on the “prize”. We spent 4-5 months working on nifty features and forgot to ask both the customer and the end-user, if they found value in what we were creating. Now we are struggling to salvage what we have and restart testing for value. Still optimistic but we had a very expensive lesson. It’s very easy to lose focus if you stay in your comfort zone and avoid regular reality checks.
